e in by an unknown mechanism. The blood and air cause the lung to collapse (''i.e.'' catamenial [[hemopneumothorax]]).<ref>^ a b Glynis D. Wallace. Living With Lung And Colon Endometriosis: Catamenial Pneumothorax. Authorhouse, 2005. {{ISBN|1-4208-8331-3}}</ref>\n\n==Diagnosis==\n[[Diagnosis]] can be hinted by high recurrence rates of lung collapse in a woman of reproductive age with endometriosis.  [[CA-125]] is elevated. Video-assisted [[thoracoscopy]] is used for confirmation.\n===Classification===\nCatamenial pneumothorax is the most common form of [[thoracic endometriosis syndrome]], which also includes [[catamenial hemothorax]], [[catamenial hemoptysis]], [[catamenial hemopneumothorax]] and [[endometriosis]] lung [[Nodule (medicine)|nodule]]s, as well as some exceptional presentations <ref name=Bricelj> Bricelj K et al. Catamenial pneumothorax since introduction of video-assisted thoracoscopic surgery : A systematic review. Wien Klin Wochenschr. 2017;129(19-20):717-726. doi: 10.1007/s00508-017-1237-4. {{PMID|28762057}}</ref>.\n\n==Treatment==\n[[Pneumothorax]] can be a [[medical emergency]], as it can become associated with decreased lung function, and if progressed to [[tension pneumothorax]], potentially fatal. In many cases, catamenial pneumothorax will resolve spontaneously and not require immediate intervention.  In more severe cases, a [[chest tube]] may be required to release air and/or blood and to allow the lung to re-expand. \n\nSurgery, hormonal treatments and combined approaches have all been proposed, with variable results in terms of short and long term outcome.<ref name=Peikert_2005>{{cite journal |vauthors=Peikert T, Gillespie DJ, Cassivi SD |title=Catamenial pneumothorax: case report and review of the literature |journal=Mayo Clinic Proceedings |volume=80 |issue=5 |pages=677\u2013680 |year=2005 |pmid=15887438 |doi=10.4065/80.5.677|doi-access=free }}</ref> Surgical removal of the endometrial tissue should be endeavoured during menstruation for optimal visualisation of the cyst.<ref name=asian>Poyraz AS, Kilic D, Hatipoglu A, Demirhan BA. A very rare entity: catamenial pneumothorax. ''Asian Cardiovasc Thorac Ann'' 2005; '''13''':271-3. {{PMID|16113003}}</ref> [[Pleurodesis]] may also be helpful. Menstruation and accompanying lung collapse can be suppressed with hormone therapy,<ref name=eMedicine>{{eMedicine|radio|563}}</ref> like with [[Leuprolide|Lupron Depot]], [[danazol]] or [[extended cycle combined oral contraceptive pill]]s, or GnRH antagonist medications. \n\n==Epidemiology==\nSome sources claim this entity represents 3 to 6% of pneumothorax in women.<ref name=\"eMedicine\" /> In regard of the low [[incidence (epidemiology)|incidence]] of primary spontaneous pneumothorax (''i.e.'' not due to surgical trauma ''etc.'') in women (about 1/100'000/year),<ref name=\"eMedicine\" /> this is a very rare condition. Hence, many basic textbooks do not mention it, and many [[Physician|doctors]] have never heard of it.  Therefore, catamenial pneumothorax is probably under-recognized.<ref name=\"chest\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n|  ICD10           = <!--{{ICD10|Xxx.x}}-->\n|  ICD9            = <!--{{ICD9|xxx}}-->\n|  ICDO            = \n|  OMIM            = 131200\n|  DiseasesDB      = \n|  MedlinePlus     = \n|  eMedicineSubj   = \n|  eMedicineTopic  = \n|  MeSH            = \n|  GeneReviewsNBK  = \n|  GeneReviewsName = \n|  Orphanet        = \n}}\n{{Respiratory pathology}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Catamenial Pneumothorax}}\n[[Category:Medical emergencies]]\n[[Category:Menstrual disorders]]\n[[Category:Diseases of pleura]]\n[[Category:Rare diseases]]\n", "name_user": "Rjwilmsi", "label": "safe", "comment": "Journal cites:, templated 4 journal cites, added 3 issue numbers", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catamenial_pneumothorax"}
{"title_page": "Grettell Valdez", "text_new": "{{Spanish name|Vald\u00e9z|Jim\u00e9nez}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Grettell Valdez\n| image        = Grettel Valdez in 2019.jpg\n| caption      = Valdez in 2019\n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1976|7|8}}<ref name=\"2.esmas.com\" />\n| birth_place  = [[Mexico City, Mexico]]<ref name=\"2.esmas.com\" />\n| residence    = \n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = 1997\u2013present\n| spouse       = {{marriage|[[Patricio Borghetti]]|2004|2010|reason=divorced}}\n| children      = 1\n}}\n'''Grettell Valdez''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8\u0261\u027eetel \u03b2al\u02c8des}};  born July 8, 1976) is a Mexican television and film [[Actor|actress]] and former fashion [[model (person)|model]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.modelsrating.com/models/grettell-valdez#.Vd-Tixxw1uc|title=Grettel Valdez modeling profile|publisher=Models Ratings }}</ref><ref name=\"2.esmas.com\">{{cite web|title=Grettell Valdez|url=http://www2.esmas.com/entretenimiento/biografias/181162/grettell-valdez/|website=2.esmas.com|publisher=[[Esmas.com]]|accessdate=22 March 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[Quer\u00e9taro]], [[Mexico]], Vald\u00e9z's first acting role was in a telenovela called [[Sin ti (TV series)|Sin ti]] between 1997 and 1998.\nIn 1998 she made a special appearance in the [[Jos\u00e9 Alberto Castro]]'s telenovela ''[[\u00c1ngela (telenovela)|\u00c1ngela]]'' as Eloisa.\nIn 1999 she made a special appearance on ''[[Por tu amor]]'' as a younger version of Isaura Espinoza as Alejandra Avell\u00e1n.\n\n=== 2000s: ''Clase 406'' and ''\u00c1ngel rebelde'' ===\nIn 2001 she again appeared in ''[[Mujer, casos de la vida real]]'' that starred [[Silvia Pinal]]. In 2002 she starred in series [[Clase 406]] as Daniela alongside [[Aar\u00f3n D\u00edaz]] and [[Dulce Mar\u00eda]].\n\nIn 2004 she starred in a [[Venezuela]]n telenovela,''[[\u00c1ngel rebelde]]'' as the protagonist alongside [[Victor Noriega]] and [[Maritza Rodriguez]].\nShe also had a supporting role in the [[Mexico|Mexican]] teen series ''[[Rebelde (Mexican telenovela)|Rebelde]]'' as Renata Lizaldi.\n\nIn 2006, she co-starred in Roberto Hern\u00e1ndez's telenovela,''[[Heridas de Amor]]'' as Pamela Altamirano.\nShe made a comeback to [[telenovela]]s in ''[[Lola, \u00e9rase una vez]]'' alongside [[Aar\u00f3n D\u00edaz]] and [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]].\n\nShe appeared in one of the episodes of ''[[Mujeres asesinas (Mexican TV series)|Mujeres asesinas]]''. In 2009, she was one of the antagonists in [[Rosy Ocampo]]'s telenovela, [[Camaleones]].\n\n=== 2010s: ''Amorcito coraz\u00f3n'' and ''Lo que la vida me rob\u00f3'' ===\nIn 2010, Carlos Moreno featured her in [[Cuando Me Enamoro (telenovela)|Cuando me enamoro]] as Matilde along with [[Silvia Navarro]] and [[Juan Soler]]. In 2011, she was one of the protagonists in Lucero Suarez's ''[[Amorcito coraz\u00f3n]]'' as Zoe Guerrero.\n\nIn July 2013, she was confirmed to star as the antagonist in Angelli Nesma's ''[[Lo que la vida me rob\u00f3]]'' alongside [[Angelique Boyer]], [[Sebasti\u00e1n Rulli]], [[Luis Roberto Guzm\u00e1n]] and [[Daniela Castro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.starmedia.com/entretenimiento/telenovelas/atacan-grettell-valdez-maria-villana-que-vida-me-robo.html|title =Atacan a Grettell Valdez (Mar\u00eda), la villana de Lo que la vida me rob\u00f3|language=Spanish|publisher=Fernanda G. Mencos}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2015, she was confirmed to star as the main antagonist in Salvador Mejia's ''[[Lo imperdonable (2015 telenovela)|Lo imperdonable]]'' as Virginia Prado-Castello alongside [[Ana Brenda Contreras]], [[Iv\u00e1n S\u00e1nchez]] and [[Sergio Sendel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://elcomercio.pe/movil/tvmas/television/grettell-valdez-no-tipica-villana-lo-imperdonable-noticia-1811639|title=Grettel Valdez sera villana en Lo imperdonable|language=Spanish|publisher=El Comercio}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nValdez married her ''[[Rebelde (Mexican telenovela)|Rebelde]]'' and ''[[Angel Rebelde]]'' co-star, the actor and singer [[Patricio Borghetti]], in 2004.<ref>{{in lang|es}} [http://www.esmas.com/espectaculos/farandula/412510.html \"Pato Borghetti y Gretel Vald\u00e9s se casan por la iglesia\"], esmas.com, 13 December 2004</ref> At the start of 2008, she announced that they were expecting their first child. She gave birth to a baby boy, Santino, on July 25, 2008.<ref>{{in lang|es}} [http://dechismes.com/nace-el-bebe-de-gretel-valdez-y-patricio-borghetti/ \"Nace el beb\u00e9 de Gretel Valdez y Patricio Borghetti\"], dechismes.com, 25 July 2008</ref> In October 2009, it was confirmed by Patricio that the two had separated and were getting a divorce. The divorce was finalized in December 2010.<ref>{{in lang|es}} [http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,1932716,00.html \"Pato Borghetti admite crisis con Grettell Valdez\"], peopleenespanol.com, 27 October 2009</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Confirmado divorcio entre Patricio Borghetti y Gretel V\u00e1ldez|url=http://www.tvyespectaculos.mx/2010/08/06/confirmado-divorcio-entre-patricio-borghetti-y-gretel-valdez/|website=tvyespectaculos.mx|accessdate=22 March 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''El duende del reloj'' \n| Iris\n| [[Short film]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Un mundo raro'' \n| Edec\u00e1n\n| \n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Sobre tus huellas'' \n| Eva\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1997 \n| ''[[Sin ti (TV series)|Sin ti]]'' \n| Unknown role\n| \n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Infierno en el para\u00edso]]'' \n| Unknown role\n| \n|-\n| 2002\u20132003\n| ''[[Clase 406]]'' \n| Daniela Jim\u00e9nez Robles\n| Main role; 56 episodes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[\u00c1ngel rebelde]]'' \n| Luc\u00eda Valderrama Covarrubias\n| Main role; 214 episodes\n|-\n| 2004\u20132006\n| ''[[Rebelde (Mexican TV series)|Rebelde]]'' \n| Renata Lizaldi\n| Recurring role\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Heridas de amor]]'' \n| Pamela Altamirano Villamil\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Lola, \u00e9rase una vez]]'' \n| Carlota Santo Domingo Torres-Oviedo\n| Antagonist\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Alma de hierro]]'' \n| Melisa\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Mujeres asesinas (Mexican TV series)|Mujeres asesinas]]'' \n| Marcela Gonz\u00e1lez\n| Episode: \"Sonia, desalmada\"\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Verano de amor]]'' \n| Perla G\u00f3mez\n| Episode: \"En fuga\"\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Camaleones]]'' \n| Silvana\n| Recurring role; 45 episodes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Tiempo final]]'' \n| Paula\n| Episode: \"El funeral\"\n|-\n| 2010\u20132011\n| ''[[Cuando me enamoro (TV series)|Cuando me enamoro]]'' \n| Matilde L\u00f3pez\n| Recurring role; 163 episodes\n|-\n| 2011\u20132012\n| ''[[Amorcito coraz\u00f3n]]'' \n| Zoe Guerrero de Garc\u00eda de Alva\n| Main role; 205 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[:es:La cl\u00ednica|La cl\u00ednica]]'' \n| Mar\u00eda Carlota / La Vagabunda\n| \n|-\n| 2013\u20132014\n| ''[[Lo que la vida me rob\u00f3]]'' \n| Mar\u00eda Zamudio\n| Main Antagonist; 137 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Lo imperdonable (2015 TV series)|Lo imperdonable]]'' \n| Virginia Prado Castelo\n| Main Antagonist; 121 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Las amazonas (Mexican TV series)|Las amazonas]]'' \n| Casandra Santos\n| Main role; 62 episodes\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Ten\u00edas que ser t\u00fa (2018 TV series)|Ten\u00edas que ser t\u00fa]]'' \n| Jeny Pineda Salgado\n| Main Antgaonist / Co-protagonist\n|-\n| 2019-2020\n| ''[[M\u00e9dicos]]'' \n| Dra. Ana Caballero\n| Main role\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|1302904}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Valdez, Gretell}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mexican telenovela actresses]]\n[[Category:Mexican television actresses]]\n[[Category:Mexican film actresses]]\n[[Category:20th-century Mexican actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Mexican actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{Spanish name|Vald\u00e9z|Jim\u00e9nez}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Grettell Valdez\n| image        = Grettel Valdez in 2019.jpg\n| caption      = Valdez in 2019\n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1976|7|8}}<ref name=\"2.esmas.com\" />\n| birth_place  = [[Mexico City, Mexico]]<ref name=\"2.esmas.com\" />\n| residence    = \n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = 1997\u2013present\n| spouse       = {{marriage|[[Patricio Borghetti]]|2004|2010|reason=divorced}}\n| children      = 1\n}}\n'''Grettell Valdez''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8\u0261\u027eetel \u03b2al\u02c8des}};  born July 8, 1976) is a Mexican television and film [[Actor|actress]] and former fashion [[model (person)|model]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.modelsrating.com/models/grettell-valdez#.Vd-Tixxw1uc|title=Grettel Valdez modeling profile|publisher=Models Ratings }}</ref><ref name=\"2.esmas.com\">{{cite web|title=Grettell Valdez|url=http://www2.esmas.com/entretenimiento/biografias/181162/grettell-valdez/|website=2.esmas.com|publisher=[[Esmas.com]]|accessdate=22 March 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[Quer\u00e9taro]], [[Mexico]], Vald\u00e9z's first acting role was in a telenovela called [[Sin ti (TV series)|Sin ti]] between 1997 and 1998.\nIn 1998 she made a special appearance in the [[Jos\u00e9 Alberto Castro]]'s telenovela ''[[\u00c1ngela (telenovela)|\u00c1ngela]]'' as Eloisa.\nIn 1999 she made a special appearance on ''[[Por tu amor]]'' as a younger version of Isaura Espinoza as Alejandra Avell\u00e1n.\n\n=== 2000s: ''Clase 406'' and ''\u00c1ngel rebelde'' ===\nIn 2001 she again appeared in ''[[Mujer, casos de la vida real]]'' that starred [[Silvia Pinal]]. In 2002 she starred in series [[Clase 406]] as Daniela alongside [[Aar\u00f3n D\u00edaz]] and [[Dulce Mar\u00eda]].\n\nIn 2004 she starred in a [[Venezuela]]n telenovela,''[[\u00c1ngel rebelde]]'' as the protagonist alongside [[Victor Noriega]] and [[Maritza Rodriguez]].\nShe also had a supporting role in the [[Mexico|Mexican]] teen series ''[[Rebelde (Mexican telenovela)|Rebelde]]'' as Renata Lizaldi.\n\nIn 2006, she co-starred in Roberto Hern\u00e1ndez's telenovela,''[[Heridas de Amor]]'' as Pamela Altamirano.\nShe made a comeback to [[telenovela]]s in ''[[Lola, \u00e9rase una vez]]'' alongside [[Aar\u00f3n D\u00edaz]] and [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]].\n\nShe appeared in one of the episodes of ''[[Mujeres asesinas (Mexican TV series)|Mujeres asesinas]]''. In 2009, she was one of the antagonists in [[Rosy Ocampo]]'s telenovela, [[Camaleones]].\n\n=== 2010s: ''Amorcito coraz\u00f3n'' and ''Lo que la vida me rob\u00f3'' ===\nIn 2010, Carlos Moreno featured her in [[Cuando Me Enamoro (telenovela)|Cuando me enamoro]] as Matilde along with [[Silvia Navarro]] and [[Juan Soler]]. In 2011, she was one of the protagonists in Lucero Suarez's ''[[Amorcito coraz\u00f3n]]'' as Zoe Guerrero.\n\nIn July 2013, she was confirmed to star as the antagonist in Angelli Nesma's ''[[Lo que la vida me rob\u00f3]]'' alongside [[Angelique Boyer]], [[Sebasti\u00e1n Rulli]], [[Luis Roberto Guzm\u00e1n]] and [[Daniela Castro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.starmedia.com/entretenimiento/telenovelas/atacan-grettell-valdez-maria-villana-que-vida-me-robo.html|title =Atacan a Grettell Valdez (Mar\u00eda), la villana de Lo que la vida me rob\u00f3|language=Spanish|publisher=Fernanda G. Mencos}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2015, she was confirmed to star as the main antagonist in Salvador Mejia's ''[[Lo imperdonable (2015 telenovela)|Lo imperdonable]]'' as Virginia Prado-Castello alongside [[Ana Brenda Contreras]], [[Iv\u00e1n S\u00e1nchez]] and [[Sergio Sendel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://elcomercio.pe/movil/tvmas/television/grettell-valdez-no-tipica-villana-lo-imperdonable-noticia-1811639|title=Grettel Valdez sera villana en Lo imperdonable|language=Spanish|publisher=El Comercio}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nValdez married her ''[[Rebelde (Mexican telenovela)|Rebelde]]'' and ''[[Angel Rebelde]]'' co-star, the actor and singer [[Patricio Borghetti]], in 2004.<ref>{{in lang|es}} [http://www.esmas.com/espectaculos/farandula/412510.html \"Pato Borghetti y Gretel Vald\u00e9s se casan por la iglesia\"], esmas.com, 13 December 2004</ref> At the start of 2008, she announced that they were expecting their first child. She gave birth to a baby boy, Santino, on July 25, 2008.<ref>{{in lang|es}} [http://dechismes.com/nace-el-bebe-de-gretel-valdez-y-patricio-borghetti/ \"Nace el beb\u00e9 de Gretel Valdez y Patricio Borghetti\"], dechismes.com, 25 July 2008</ref> In October 2009, it was confirmed by Patricio that the two had separated and were getting a divorce. The divorce was finalized in December 2010.<ref>{{in lang|es}} [http://www.peopleenespanol.com/pespanol/articles/0,22490,1932716,00.html \"Pato Borghetti admite crisis con Grettell Valdez\"], peopleenespanol.com, 27 October 2009</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Confirmado divorcio entre Patricio Borghetti y Gretel V\u00e1ldez|url=http://www.tvyespectaculos.mx/2010/08/06/confirmado-divorcio-entre-patricio-borghetti-y-gretel-valdez/|website=tvyespectaculos.mx|accessdate=22 March 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''El duende del reloj'' \n| Iris\n| [[Short film]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Un mundo raro'' \n| Edec\u00e1n\n| \n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Sobre tus huellas'' \n| Eva\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1997 \n| ''[[Sin ti (TV series)|Sin ti]]'' \n| Unknown role\n| \n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Infierno en el para\u00edso]]'' \n| Unknown role\n| \n|-\n| 2002\u20132003\n| ''[[Clase 406]]'' \n| Daniela Jim\u00e9nez Robles\n| Main role; 56 episodes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[\u00c1ngel rebelde]]'' \n| Luc\u00eda Valderrama Covarrubias\n| Main role; 214 episodes\n|-\n| 2004\u20132006\n| ''[[Rebelde (Mexican TV series)|Rebelde]]'' 