orarily closed,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis |title=Coronavirus: European borders likely to remain open despite crisis in Italy, observers say |date=7 March 2020 |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315040544/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the [[European Union]] by 13 March continued to reject the idea of suspending the [[Schengen Area|Schengen free travel area]] and introducing border controls with Italy.<ref name=\"dw-schengen\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |title=Coronavirus: EU rules out Schengen border closures amid Italy outbreak |date=24 February 2020 |publisher=Deutsche Welle |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313142436/https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |title=Salvini and Le Pen Don't Have a Coronavirus Cure |date=25 February 2020 |work=Bloomberg |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227122244/https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |title=Coronavirus: Europe's open borders threatened by spread of disease |date=28 February 2020 |work=The Independent |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317173409/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |title=Commission chief warns against unilateral virus travel bans |date=13 March 2020 |work=[[EURACTIV]] |access-date=18 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318195056/https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The deputy leader of the Swiss [[Ticino League]], Lorenzo Quadri, by 29 February had criticised the decision: \"It is alarming that the dogma of wide-open borders is considered a priority.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |title=Coronavirus Nightmare Could Be the End for Europe's Borderless Dream |date=26 February 2020 |work=The New York Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303055756/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> United States President [[Donald Trump]] said by 12 March the European Union had \"failed to take the same precautions and restrict travel from China and other hot spots\" as the US had implemented.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |title=In dramatic step, Trump restricts travel from Europe to US to fight coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314140433/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Trump also said that \"As a result a large number of new clusters in the United States were seeded by travellers from Europe.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: What you need to know about Trump's Europe travel ban |url=https://www.thelocal.dk/20200312/trump-imposes-travel-ban-from-europe-over-coronavirus-outbreak |work=The Local |date=12 March 2020}}</ref> Research on [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|coronavirus genomes]] indicates the majority of COVID-19 cases in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|New York]] came from European travelers, rather than directly from China or any other Asian country.<ref>{{cite news |title=Studies Show N.Y. Outbreak Originated in Europe|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/08/us/coronavirus-live-updates.html |work=The New York Times |date=April 8, 2020}}</ref> \n\nBy 9 March Czech Prime Minister [[Andrej Babi\u0161]] stated that \"European countries cannot ban the entry of Italian citizens within the Schengen area. The only possible way is to have the Italian prime minister call on his fellow citizens to refrain from traveling to other countries of the European Union.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |title=Czech PM: Italians Should Be Banned From Travelling Due to Coronavirus |date=9 March 2020 |work=SchengenVisaInfo.com |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323171345/https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter Czech Republic, Slovakia, Poland and Denmark announced complete closure of their national borders, the [[European Commission]] President [[Ursula von der Leyen]] said by 12 March that \"Certain controls may be justified, but general travel bans are not seen as being the most effective by the World Health Organization. Moreover, they have a strong social and economic impact, they disrupt people\u2019s lives and business across the borders.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Denmark, Poland and Czechs seal borders over coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314202823/https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> European Union leaders condemned the US decision to restrict travel from Europe to the United States. [[European Council]] President [[Charles Michel]] and Ursula von der Leyen said in a joint statement: \"The European Union disapproves of the fact that the US decision to impose a travel ban was taken unilaterally and without consultation.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |title=EU condemns Trump travel ban from Europe as virus spreads |date=12 March 2020 |work=Associated Press (AP) |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313140528/https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ursula von der Leyen admitted by 17 March that \"all of us who are not experts initially underestimated the coronavirus.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |title=Politicians 'underestimated' virus threat, von der Leyen admits |date=18 March 2020 |work=Euractiv |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319152350/https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Italian government has criticised EU's lack of solidarity with Italy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |title=The EU Is Abandoning Italy in Its Hour of Need |date=14 March 2020 |work=Foreign Policy |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315112947/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |title=Italy criticises EU for being slow to help over coronavirus epidemic |date=11 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313000621/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Italy wonders where Europe's solidarity is as coronavirus strains show |date=13 March 2020 |work=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315154437/https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |title=Italy criticizes EU for not responding its call for help, 'only China responded bilaterally' |date=12 March 2020 |work=CGTN |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316024124/https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |archive-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Politico'' reported on 7 March that \"EU countries have so far refused Italy's plea for help fighting coronavirus, as national capitals worry that they may need to stockpile face masks and other medical gear to help their own citizens, officials and diplomats said.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |title=Europe fails to help Italy in coronavirus fight |date=7 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317055659/https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Maurizio Massari, Italy's ambassador to the EU, said that \"Only China responded bilaterally. Certainly, this is not a good sign of European solidarity.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\" /> [[Serbia]]n President [[Aleksandar Vu\u010di\u0107]] said that \"European solidarity does not exist. That was a fairy tale.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |title=China is winning the coronavirus propaganda war |date=18 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322203919/https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n[[File:Reivindicaciones 8M (49637966373).jpg|thumb|[[International Women's Day]] march in M\u00e9rida, Spain, 8 March<ref>{{cite news |title=Thousands March in Spain on Women's Day Despite Coronavirus Fears |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2020-03-08/thousands-march-in-spain-on-womens-day-despite-coronavirus-fears |date=8 March 2020 |work=[[US News]] |agency=[[Reuters]]}}</ref>]]\nAccording to ''The Guardian'', [[Spain]]'s initially slow response to the coronavirus caused the epidemic to become severe even though it did not share a land border with Italy or other severely affected countries.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tremlett |first1=Giles |title=How did Spain get its coronavirus response so wrong? |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/26/spain-coronavirus-response-analysis |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref> An analysis in ''[[Vox (website)|Vox]]'' hypothesised that the minority government did not want to risk its hold on power by banning large gatherings early; Prime Minister [[Pedro S\u00e1nchez]] initially defended his decision to allow large gatherings to continue.<ref name=Vox>{{cite news |last1=Ward |first1=Alex |title=How Spain's coronavirus outbreak got so bad so fast |url=https://www.vox.com/2020/3/20/21183315/coronavirus-spain-outbreak-cases-tests |work=Vox |date=20 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe planned [[NATO]] \u201c[[List of NATO exercises|Defender 2020]]\u201d military exercise in Germany, Poland, and the Baltic states,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |title=How coronavirus derailed the largest Nato exercise in 25 years |date=20 March 2020 |work=The Spectator |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102257/https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the largest NATO war manoeuvres since the end of the [[Cold War]], was to be held on a reduced scale because of the coronavirus pandemic.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |title=NATO scales down exercises due to coronavirus |date=19 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102254/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The [[Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament]]'s general secretary [[Kate Hudson (activist)|Kate Hudson]] critisiced the Defender 2020 exercise: \"In the current public-health crisis, it jeopardises the lives not only of the troops from the US and the many European countries participating but the inhabitants of the countries in which they are operating.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |title=Nato must end 'dangerous and irresponsible' military exercise on Russia's border, campaigners say |date=18 March 2020 |work=Morning Star |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320010441/https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[PREPARE]] (EU PREPARE project)\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"OKOpress_Szumowski_EU_claims\">{{cite news | last1= Pa\u0144kowska | first1= Maria | language =pl | title= Szumowski krytykuje UE: 'Nie ma tej europejskiej solidarno\u015bci'. To wielopi\u0119trowy fa\u0142sz |trans-title = Szumowski criticise the EU: 'There is no European solidarity'. Which is false at many levels<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | date= 2020-03-26 |newspaper= [[OKO.press]] | url= https://oko.press/szumowski-krytykuje-ue-nie-ma-tej-europejskiej-solidarnosci-to-wielopietrowy-falsz/ |quote= Bo jak by\u015bmy czekali na inne kraje, na Europ\u0119, na \u015bwiat, to by\u015bmy si\u0119 obudzili bez \u015brodk\u00f3w, a dooko\u0142a wszyscy by te \u015brodki sobie zakupili ... \u017beby by\u0142a jasno\u015b\u0107, to nie jest tak, \u017ce my ten sprz\u0119t mamy w Europie, \u017ce s\u0105 jego nieograniczone ilo\u015bci. ... Bo niestety tutaj centralne zakupy zawiod\u0142y, nie ma tej europejskiej solidarno\u015bci.  |accessdate=2020-03-26 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200326225848/https://oko.press/szumowski-krytykuje-ue-nie-ma-tej-europejskiej-solidarnosci-to-wielopietrowy-falsz/ |archivedate= 2020-03-26 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped --> |url-access = <!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free -->}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://corona.arrangy.com Worldwide Coronavirus Map, confirmed Cases] \u2013 Map the route paths of coronavirus confirmed cases.\n* [https://systems.jhu.edu/research/public-health/ncov/ ncov \u2013 CSSE] \u2013 Map of the expansion of the virus in Europe and in the world\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Europe|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in Europe]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by continent|Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe| ]]\n", "name_user": "Ondoro", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStatistics by country and territory", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Europe"}
{"title_page": "Ranjith Premasiri Madalana", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox military person\n| name                      = Sniper Nero - Ranjith Premasiri{{KIA}}\n| honorific_suffix          = DPS, PBP\n| nickname                  = Nero\n| image                     = [[File:A known photograph of Nero - Ranjith Premasiri Madalana (Red circle).jpg|thumb|]]\n| image_size                = \n| alt                       = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_date                = \n| death_date                = 28 April 2009\n| birth_place               = [[Pallama]], [[Sri Lanka]]\n| death_place               = \n| placeofburial             = \n| placeofburial_label       = \n| placeofburial_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline,title}} -->\n| birth_name                = Ranjith Premasiri Madalana\n| allegiance                = {{flag|Sri Lanka}}\n| branch                    = {{army|Sri Lanka}}\n| serviceyears              = 1991\u20132009\n| rank                      = [[File:02. SLA-CPL.svg|10px]] [[Corporal]]\n| servicenumber             = <!--Do not use data from primary sources such as service records.-->\n| unit                      = [[Sri Lanka Army Volunteer Force]]<br>5th Battalion [[Gajaba Regiment]]\n| commands                  = \n| battles                   = [[Sri Lankan Civil War]]\n*[[Operation Riviresa]]\n*[[Eelam War IV]]\n| battles_label             = \n| awards                    = [[File:Desha Putra Sammanaya ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[Desha Putra Sammanaya]]<br>[[File:Purna Bhumi Padakkama ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[Purna Bhumi Padakkama]]<br>[[File:North and East Operations Medal ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[North and East Operations Medal]]<br>[[File:Riviresa Campaign Services Medal ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[Riviresa Campaign Services Medal]]<br>[[File:Sri Lanka Army 50th Anniversary Medal ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[Sri Lanka Army 50th Anniversary Medal]]<br>[[File:50th Independence Anniversary Commemoration Medal.svg|25px]] [[50th Independence Anniversary Commemoration Medal]]\n}}\n\n'''Ranjith Premasiri Madalana''' alias \"Nero\" was a decorated [[Sri Lanka Army]] sniper with 217 confirmed LTTE kills during the Eelam War.<ref>{{cite web | url =http://infolanka.asia/eelam-war/a-soldiers-view/how-the-ltte-was-military-defeated-a-soldiers-view-part-seven| title=How the LTTE was 'military' defeated: A Soldier\u2019s view - Part Seven |work =infolanka.asia |publisher = Infolanka |accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nHe was killed on 28 April 2009, 20 days before the end of the conflict.<ref>[http://www.lankanewspapers.com/news/2010/4/56061_space.html&page= Let us remember Nero: the Phussadeva of our time, the archer who never missed his mark lankanewspapers.com - April 28, 2010]</ref>\n\nHe is also listed in world sniper list and is ranked at 5th place on it.\n\n==Military career==\nAt the height of the Sri Lankan Civil War, Premasiri joined the Sri Lanka Army Volunteer Force in 1991 at the age of 22. After his training at the Diyathalawa Army base, he was attached to the 5th Battalion of the Gajaba Regiment.\n\nAfter completing the Sri Lanka Army 8th sniper course, he joined the Army snipers in 2000.\n\nHe was injured several times during his service but insisted on serving in active duty.\n\nOn 28 April 2009, LTTE combatants took hiding among Tamil refugees that were fleeing to government controlled areas in Puthumathalan. While tracking the combatants, Corporal Premasiri was killed by an LTTE sniper.\n\nThe Sri Lankan Civil war ended on 18 May 2009 just 20 days after Corporal Premasiri's death. At the time of his death, he had served 18 years in the Sri Lanka Army and 9 years of it as a sniper with 217 confirmed kills.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of snipers]]\n* [[List of Sri Lankan military personnel]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Madalana, Ranjith Premasiri}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:2009 deaths]]\n[[Category:Military personnel killed in action]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan military personnel killed in action]]\n[[Category:Sinhalese military personnel]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox military person\n| name                      = Ranjith Premasiri{{KIA}}\n| honorific_suffix          = DPS, PBP\n| nickname                  = Nero\n| image                     = [[File:A known photograph of Nero - Ranjith Premasiri Madalana (Red circle).jpg|thumb|]]\n| image_size                = \n| alt                       = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_date                = \n| death_date                = 28 April 2009\n| birth_place               = [[Pallama]], [[Sri Lanka]]\n| death_place               = \n| placeofburial             = \n| placeofburial_label       = \n| placeofburial_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline,title}} -->\n| birth_name                = Ranjith Premasiri Madalana\n| allegiance                = {{flag|Sri Lanka}}\n| branch                    = {{army|Sri Lanka}}\n| serviceyears              = 1991\u20132009\n| rank                      = [[File:02. SLA-CPL.svg|10px]] [[Corporal]]\n| servicenumber             = <!--Do not use data from primary sources such as service records.-->\n| unit                      = [[Sri Lanka Army Volunteer Force]]<br>5th Battalion [[Gajaba Regiment]]\n| commands                  = \n| battles                   = [[Sri Lankan Civil War]]\n*[[Operation Riviresa]]\n*[[Eelam War IV]]\n| battles_label             = \n| awards                    = [[File:Desha Putra Sammanaya ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[Desha Putra Sammanaya]]<br>[[File:Purna Bhumi Padakkama ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[Purna Bhumi Padakkama]]<br>[[File:North and East Operations Medal ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[North and East Operations Medal]]<br>[[File:Riviresa Campaign Services Medal ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[Riviresa Campaign Services Medal]]<br>[[File:Sri Lanka Army 50th Anniversary Medal ribbon bar.svg|25px]] [[Sri Lanka Army 50th Anniversary Medal]]<br>[[File:50th Independence Anniversary Commemoration Medal.svg|25px]] [[50th Independence Anniversary Commemoration Medal]]\n}}\n\n'''Ranjith Premasiri Madalana''' alias \"Nero\" was a decorated [[Sri Lanka Army]] sniper with 217 confirmed LTTE kills during the Eelam War.<ref>{{cite web | url =http://infolanka.asia/eelam-war/a-soldiers-view/how-the-ltte-was-military-defeated-a-soldiers-view-part-seven| title=How the LTTE was 'military' defeated: A Soldier\u2019s view - Part Seven |work =infolanka.asia |publisher = Infolanka |accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nHe was killed on 28 April 2009, 20 days before the end of the conflict.<ref>[http://www.lankanewspapers.com/news/2010/4/56061_space.html&page= Let us remember Nero: the Phussadeva of our time, the archer who never missed his mark lankanewspapers.com - April 28, 2010]</ref>\n\nHe is also listed in world sniper list and is ranked at 5th place on it.\n\n==Military career==\nAt the height of the Sri Lankan Civil War, Premasiri joined the Sri Lanka Army Volunteer Force in 1991 at the age of 22. After his training at the Diyathalawa Army base, he was attached to the 5th Battalion of the Gajaba Regiment.\n\nAfter completing the Sri Lanka Army 8th sniper course, he joined the Army snipers in 2000.\n\nHe was injured several times during his service but insisted on serving in active duty.\n\nOn 28 April 2009, LTTE combatants took hiding among Tamil refugees that were fleeing to government controlled areas in Puthumathalan. While tracking the combatants, Corporal Premasiri was killed by an LTTE sniper.\n\nThe Sri Lankan Civil war ended on 18 May 2009 just 20 days after Corporal Premasiri's death. At the time of his death, he had served 18 years in the Sri Lanka Army and 9 years of it as a sniper with 217 confirmed kills.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of snipers]]\n* [[List of Sri Lankan military personnel]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Madalana, Ranjith Premasiri}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:2009 deaths]]\n[[Category:Military personnel killed in action]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan military personnel killed in action]]\n[[Category:Sinhalese military personnel]]\n", "name_user": "Chandi28", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranjith_Premasiri_Madalana"}
{"title_page": "Legislative violence", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Short description|Violence in legislative bodies}}\n{{Use American English|date = February 2019}}\n[[File:Southern Chivalry.jpg|thumb|A [[political cartoon]] depicting U.S. Democratic congressman [[Preston Brooks]]'s attack on Republican congressman [[Charles Sumner]], an example of legislative violence.]]\n'''Legislative violence''' broadly refers to any [[violence|violent]] clashes between members of a [[legislature]], often physically, inside the legislature and triggered by divisive issues and tight votes. Such clashes have occurred in many countries across time, and notable incidents still regularly occur.\n\nAlthough the sight of brawling politicians is incongruous with a legislature's stately image, its occupants, like in any other workplace, are still prone to [[stress (biology)|stress]] and [[anger]]. The confrontational nature of politics, regardless of their location, and the high stakes involved often add to the simmering tensions.<ref name=\"bbc 2004\">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/3560977.stm \"When politicians attack...\"], [[BBC News]], 23 March 2004.</ref> \n[[Galusha A. Grow]], no stranger to legislative violence, described the precursors thus:<ref>{{cite news|author=[[Galusha A. Grow]] |title=The Last Days of the Duello in Congress |work=[[The Saturday Evening Post]] |volume=172 |issue=2 |year=1900 |page=1194}}</ref>{{Quote\n|text=[[Crowd]] some hundreds of men together on a hot afternoon or night; fill them with the fire of partisan [[passion (emotion)|ardor]]; perplex them with doubt as to the personal gain or loss that may follow their vote on the question at issue, and instill them with [[envy]] of, and ill-will toward, their fellows, and you have abundant material for a row. All that is needed is an excuse, and that is too often found.}}\n\n{{TOC limit|2}}\n\n== Afghanistan ==\n=== 5 July 2011 ===\nNazifa Zaki and Hamida Ahmadzai fought over rocket attacks into Afghanistan from Pakistan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-south-asia-14047444|title=Boycott after brawl by Afghan MPs|date=2011-07-06|access-date=2019-02-07}}</ref>\n\n== Algeria ==\n=== 30 November 2015 ===\nA tax bill sparked brawls in the [[parliament of Algeria]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/variety/2015/12/01/Video-Tax-bill-sparks-brawls-in-Algeria-s-parliament.html|title=Video: Tax bill sparks brawls in Algeria's parliament|publisher=Al Arabiya|access-date=2019-02-07}}</ref>\n\n== Ancient Rome ==\n{{unreferenced section|date=October 2015}}\n[[File:Vincenzo Camuccini - La morte di Cesare.jpg|upright=1.3|thumb|''Morte de C\u00e9sare'' (Death of Caesar) by [[Vincenzo Camuccini]]]]\nRoman general and [[Roman dictator|dictator]] [[Julius Caesar]] was famously [[Assassination of Julius Caesar|assassinated]] by a group of senators on the [[Ides of March]], 44 BC during a meeting of the [[Roman Senate]]. The senators, led by [[Gaius Cassius Longinus|Cassius]] and [[Marcus Junius Brutus|Brutus]] and calling themselves [[Liberatores]], had conspired in secret to kill Caesar and considered various ways to do so. Ultimately, they decided to kill him during a meeting of the senate, since only senators would be allowed in the meeting and Caesar would be alone. The senators drafted a fake petition requesting that Caesar hand over power to senate; Caesar called a meeting of the senate to read it. When Caesar met the senators at the [[Theatre of Pompey]], they stabbed him repeatedly with daggers concealed under their [[toga]]s, killing him. Caesar's assassination led to a [[civil war]] for control of the [[Roman Republic|republic]], ending ultimately with the rise of [[Augustus|Caesar Augustus]] and the founding of the [[Roman Empire]].\n\n== Armenia ==\nLegislative violence has happened in Armenia.<ref>[https://news.am/eng/news/141650.html Fight breaks in Armenian parliament]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.arminfo.info/full_news.php?id=27607&lang=3|title=Arminfo: Another fight occurred in the Armenian parliament: At this time RPA deputy Artashes Geghamyan and oppositionist Nikol Pashinyan met in hand-to-hand fight|website=arminfo.info|access-date=2019-02-07}}</ref><ref>[https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-female-legislator-attacked-brawl-sewage-smell-city-council/29037927.html Female Legislator Attacked In Brawl Over Yerevan Sewage Water ]</ref>\n\n== Australia ==\n===13 February 2019 ===\n[[Brian Burston]] and [[James Ashby]] have clashed in The Great Hall amid claims of sexual harassment.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/feb/14/blood-on-the-door-24-hours-of-chaos-australian-politics Blood on the door: 24 hours of chaos in Australian politics]</ref><ref>[https://www.news24.com/World/News/police-investigate-australia-parliament-brawl-20190214 Police investigate Australia parliament brawl]</ref><ref>[https://ewn.co.za/2019/02/14/police-investigate-aussie-parliament-brawl Police investigate Aussie Parliament brawl]</ref>\n\n== Bolivia ==\n=== 27 October 2007 ===\nIn 2007 a fight broke out in the lower chamber of the national legislature of [[Bolivia]], [[Chamber of Deputies of Bolivia|the Chamber of Deputies]]. The fight erupted during a debate over whether or not to try four judges on corruption charges.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/7695263.stm | work=BBC News | title=Fights in Bolivian parliament | date=28 October 2008}}</ref><ref>[http://metro.co.uk/2007/08/23/fists-fly-as-politicians-fight-dirty-70663/ Fists fly as politicians fight dirty]</ref><ref>[https://www.express.co.uk/videos/107757/Bolivia-Parliament-fight-errupts Bolivia - Parliament fight errupts]</ref>\n\n==Bosnia and Herzegovina==\n=== 31 July 2019 ===\nFollowing an intense debate in the Council of the [[Bosansko-podrinjska \u017eupanija|Bosnian-Podrinje Canton]] in city of [[Gora\u017ede]], councilor Daliborka Milovi\u0107, who was also the president of the Liberal Party, had thrown a plastic water bottle, hitting Edita Veli\u0107, a member of [[Democratic Front (Bosnia and Herzegovina)|Democratic Front]] in the process, who was at the time, the Chairman of the Council, after a disagreement on drafting a new law. Following the event, Milovi\u0107 was promptly escorted out of the building by the local municipal police.<ref name=\"translate.google.com\">https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=bs&tl=en&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oslobodjenje.ba%2Fvijesti%2Fbih%2Fvideo-haos-u-skupstini-bpk-a-zastupnica-flasom-pogodila-predsjedavajucu-a-evo-sta-su-poslije-incidenta-porucile-jedna-drugoj-478193</ref>\n\n=== 23 December 2019 ===\nDra\u0161ko Stanivukovi\u0107, a prominent member of the [[Party of Democratic Progress|PDP]], was initially scolded by the Milorad Dodik's right-wing SNSD-dominated club for various provocations aimed at the current government of the Republika Srpska. Being an MP, he had commonly presented his ideas which many, at the time, had considered provocative. Two days before Christmas, on 23rd December 2019, Stanivukovi\u0107 was physically assaulted by [[Dragan Luka\u010d]] of SNSD, who has been the Minister of Interior of the Republic of Srpska since 2014. Moments before the confrontation, Luka\u010d warned Stanivukovi\u0107 to cease his provocations aimed at the government, warning him in the process that he's going to \"End up on the floor, just like the hand-held flags of the NATO-pact which he had presented inside of the assembly hall. Following his statement, Luka\u010d had asked Stanivukovi\u0107, who had by now been walking around the National Assembly hall carrying hand-held flags of the NATO-pact, to approach him. Stanivukovi\u0107 did so, and after brief exchange words, Luka\u010d hit him on the head with his right fist. The event was broadcast live on the [[Radio Televizija Republike Srpske|Radio Television of the Republic of Srpska]]. This happened in the wake of events where the Bosnian three-men presidency had unanimously agreed to sign the Reform Program, which is widely speculated to be the ANP agreement under disguise.  With the signing of this agreement, the Bosnian Government will be able to pursue its NATO-membership. Following the event, Luka\u010d would go on to apologize to the mass public, but not to Stanivukovi\u0107 in particular. The case is currently under an investigation.<ref name=\"translate.google.com\"/>\n\n== Canada ==\n=== 5 December 2012 ===\n[[New Democratic Party]] House Leader [[Nathan Cullen]] attempted to delay the passing of a Conservative budget bill, leading to a threatening confrontation between Conservative Government House Leader Peter Van Loan and NDP leader [[Tom Mulcair]], described in the media as a \"near-brawl\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thechronicleherald.ca/canada/221502-near-brawl-erupts-in-house-of-commons|title=Near-brawl erupts in House of Commons|date=5 December 2012|work=The Chronicle Herald}}</ref>\n\n=== 18 May 2016 ===\nBefore a vote in the House of Commons [[Prime Minister]] [[Justin Trudeau]] \"manhandled\" Conservative Party Opposition [[Whip (politics)|Whip]] [[Gord Brown]] and inadvertently elbowed [[New Democratic Party|NDP]] MP [[Ruth Ellen Brosseau]]. The incident went on to be known as \"[[Elbowgate]]\" and officially known in the House of Commons as \"the matter of the physical molestation of the Member from Berthier\u2014Maskinong\u00e9\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/news/canada/canadian-politics/trudeau-accused-of-manhandling-mp-as-tempers-flare-in-house-of-commons|title=Chaos in the House: Trudeau accused of 'manhandling' MP as tempers flare|date=18 May 2016|work=National Post}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ourcommons.ca/Committees/en/PROC/StudyActivity?studyActivityId=8940811|title=PROC - Question of privilege (physical molestation of the Member from Berthier\u2014Maskinong\u00e9)|website=ourcommons.ca|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>\n\n== Czech Republic ==\nCzech Health Mi